document_title: Late stage cervical cancer (4): Signs and treatment
subsection_content: Late-stage cervical cancer (stage IV) is the most severe stage. Malignant cells have spread to organs outside the cervix and uterus such as the bladder, rectum, bones, lungs, liver, etc.
subsection_title: ung thu co tu cung giai doan cuoi.json. What is late-stage cervical cancer?
subsection_data:
ung thu co tu cung giai doan cuoi.json. What is late-stage cervical cancer?
Late-stage cervical cancer (stage IV) is the most severe stage. Malignant cells have spread to organs outside the cervix and uterus such as the bladder, rectum, bones, lungs, liver, etc.
